cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the application of computer vision techniques for biometric recognition, specifically sclera recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as Fully Convolutional Networks (FCN) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN), which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of two databases, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and the topic of biometric recognition could also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
